hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Dispersion relation for sloshing modes $k_n=\frac{n\pi}{L}$ in finite depth $H$ with surface tension $\sigma$ is
$$\omega_n^2=\bigl(gk_n+\tfrac{\sigma}{\rho}k_n^3\bigr)\tanh(k_nH).$$
2. For the fundamental mode $n=1$, set $k=\pi/L$. Then
$$\omega_{1,\text{deep}}^2=\bigl(gk+\tfrac{\sigma}{\rho}k^3\bigr)\,,\quad
\omega_{1,\text{shallow}}^2=\bigl(gk+\tfrac{\sigma}{\rho}k^3\bigr)\,kH.$$
3. Form the ratio of squared frequencies:
$$\frac{\omega_{1,\text{deep}}^2}{\omega_{1,\text{shallow}}^2}
=\frac{\bigl(gk+\tfrac{\sigma}{\rho}k^3\bigr)}{\bigl(gk+\tfrac{\sigma}{\rho}k^3\bigr)\,kH}
=\frac{1}{kH}
=\frac{1}{(\pi/L)\,H}
=\frac{L}{\pi H}.$$
4. Taking the square-root gives
$$\frac{\omega_{1,\text{deep}}}{\omega_{1, \text{shallow}}}
=\sqrt{\frac{L}{\pi H}}\,. $$
